history.content: 189 and 61C have a relatively higher workload. You can definitely take both at the same time, but if you do, you probably should stick to those only and take no other tech classes. 189 is a great class, just make sure you have multi-variable + linear algebra background, and 61C may be fun if you like low-level stuff. 188 won't help for 189, so either way if you take it later or now it doesn't really matter.

Would it be wise to take CS61C and CS189 at the same time? Most likely along with humanities course and/or maybe a Statistics course? Does anyone have experience doing this? Also, how useful is it to take 189 the semester after 188? Or would taking 189 a few semesters later after 188 be considered ok?

Thanks!
history.subject: CS189 and CS61C
